column5: I want to add I pilot to my trolling motor, and that's really all. I spent a bundle last year...has anyone used the add on package?
I would like a green late 2000s arctic cat 450-550 atv, and want to try a Gary Loomis Edge rod
I asked for a ZR 9000 Thundercat but Santa cheaped out and brought me this.  ????

This post is a baited question (no pun there I swear...). Honestly zero (currently) here unless I win the lotto...  and YEAH I know I need to buy a ticket to have a chance to win... Chris, Santa wanted a "happy home" and not a Chris pull's his arms off with a ton of power home I bet
Sweet green machine Chris!  If it can be worked out I'd like to go from a 16 foot Rebel XL and into an 1875 ProGuide or Competitor 185. Tiller!!!  That is all.
Got almost everything I need.  Did pretty well at Christmas though!

I'm pretty well set up for open water, but adding Ipilot to my 55 lb MinnKota would be awesome.  I hope someone who has added I pilot to an existing electric troller replies to your question.  I'll be watching this topic.
That Pro Guide is a sweet set up. A couple of my buddies have the 2075 version.
I got new fish finding toys to strap on my helm.

It's early but already acquired  For the soft water season - 2014 Lund pro guide 1675 - Minnkota Ulterra - Lowrance HDS 12 Gen2 touch  For the hardwater season - 1998 Skidoo Touring SLE 500  Also headed to Mexico in 2 weeks.  Not a bad start! Going to make 2017 count!
One of these bad boys! hahaha, hopefully this guy gets his business goin internationally!
got a 7 ft carrot styx and bait casting reel for xmas. can't wait to put them to the test
I may have to pick up some new batteries for my wheelchair and scooter!
I would love to get a bandsaw... if I could afford it lol
I'd need a lottery win for the things on my wish list.
I'd need a lottery win for the things on my wish list.  You and I both need to be my buddy. He won $1,000,000 on Friday night.
Just ordered an Avet reel for my laker trolling stick. That US exchange rate though.
I would love to get a bandsaw... if I could afford it lol Want me to see if my dad still has his?  He never uses it if he still has it.  It would be a deal too...  I'll pm you

At my age the wish list is short, I've pretty well had them all at some point, no airplane though, was close to sharing a Piper Cherokee 140 some 40 years ago. I have most all the toys for getting to and finding fish, now I need some kind of toy to catch em'. Last season was the worst since I first wet a line.
